Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @onion{1}(diced) into ½-inch pieces. Core, deseed, and dice @green bell pepper{1}(diced) into ½-inch pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #medium pot{} (large pot for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, onion, and bell pepper; stir to combine.

Season with @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until beef is cooked through and veggies are tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @tomato paste{1} to pot with beef and veggies; cook, stirring occasionally, until tomato paste darkens in color, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @marinara{5%ounce}, @beef stock concentrate{2}, @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, and 2 cups water (4 cups for 4 servings). Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to medium low. Cook until couscous is tender and soup has thickened slightly, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> TIP: If there's excess grease on the surface of the soup, carefully skim it off.

Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Divide soup between bowls and serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.